无标签
猿人学爬虫
发布日期:   2021-08-19

前言

js 混淆 - 回溯

这是一道js 混淆的中等难度题,下面我们来看看如何进行逆向它，最后拿到数据

思路

查看请求

断点查看下

发现重要的一些参数

window.i 是点击数+时间戳。并会一直拼接上一次    //"1-1629355112000|"
window.o 是
而q 就是window.i


page 则是window.page。为请求页码数

m 怎么时加密值。点击进入这个r 函数

把源码拖下来放入webstorm进行调试

js源码调试

表情包解密下

发现这么多表情包其实就就是一个赋值运算window.o = 1;

运算下发现window未定义

window = global;

再次运行下

搜索全局Message too long for RSA说明之前的都运行了

那么接下来关注下try....catch 之类的语句。很多时候重要代码放在try 语句中。目的是防止未知错误

果然发现不远处就出现了一段可疑代码

粘贴加密代码出现这个false。

再断点调试下看下重要参数

发现都未定义。这怎么可能？我们之前应该知道运行后定义应该为false的。那么是否加密的那段代码里其实是有检测的东西,我们不得而知。我们直接改为false看下

调试出结果了

放到代码里跑下发现真的撞了鬼

最后多方求证是execjs调用这个js 会有编码问题。我的乖乖，只能感叹作者牛，那么就架起来使用express架起来远程调用呗

                    function Gt(t, e) {
                        var i, s, n = t.bitLength(), r = m(1);
                        if (0 >= n)
                            return r;

                        var o = new Array
                            , a = 3

                        i > 1) {
                            var u = y();

                                o[a] = y(),

                            for (n >= c ? d = t[h] >> n - c & l : (d = (t[h] & (1 << n + 1) - 1) << c - n,
                            h > 0 && (d |= t[h - 1] >> this.DB + n - c)),
                                     a = i; 0 == (1 & d);)

                                --h),
                                f)

                                    f = !1;
                            else {
                                for (; a > 1;)
                                    s.sqrTo(r, g),
                                        s.sqrTo(g, r),
                                        a -= 2;

                                    r = g,
                                    g = p),
                                    s.mulTo(g, o[d], r)
                            }
                            for (; h >= 0 && 0 == (t[h] & 1 << n);)
                                s.sqrTo(r, g),
                                    p = r,
                                    r = g,
                                    g = p,
                                --n < 0 && (n = this.DB - 1,
                                    --h)
                        }
                        return s.revert(r)
                    }

                    function Yt(t) {
                        var e = this.s < 0 ? this.negate() : this.clone()
                            , i = t.s < 0 ? t.negate() : t.clone();

                            var s = e;
                            e = i,
                                i = s
                        }

                            , r = i.getLowestSetBit();

                        for (r > n && (r = n),
                             r > 0 && (e.rShiftTo(r, e),
                                 i.rShiftTo(r, i)); e.signum() > 0;)
                            (n = e.getLowestSetBit()) > 0 && e.rShiftTo(n, e),
                            (n = i.getLowestSetBit()) > 0 && i.rShiftTo(n, i),
                                e.compareTo(i) >= 0 ? (e.subTo(i, e),
                                    e.rShiftTo(1, e)) : (i.subTo(e, i),

                        return r > 0 && i.lShiftTo(r, i),
                            i
                    }

                    function Wt(t) {
                        if (0 >= t)

                            if (0 == e)
                                i = this[0] % t;
                            else

                                    i = (e * i + this[s]) % t;

                    }

                    function Zt(t) {
                        var e = t.isEven();
                        if (this.isEven() && e || 0 == t.signum())
                            return b.ZERO;
                        for (var i = t.clone(), s = this.clone(), n = m(1), r = m(0), o = m(0), a = m(1); 0 != i.signum();) {
                            for (; i.isEven();)
                                i.rShiftTo(1, i),
                                    e ? (n.isEven() && r.isEven() || (n.addTo(this, n),
                                        r.subTo(t, r)),
                                        n.rShiftTo(1, n)) : r.isEven() || r.subTo(t, r),
                                    r.rShiftTo(1, r);
                            for (; s.isEven();)
                                s.rShiftTo(1, s),
                                    e ? (o.isEven() && a.isEven() || (o.addTo(this, o),
                                        a.subTo(t, a)),
                                        o.rShiftTo(1, o)) : a.isEven() || a.subTo(t, a),
                                    a.rShiftTo(1, a);
                            i.compareTo(s) >= 0 ? (i.subTo(s, i),
                            e && n.subTo(o, n),
                                r.subTo(a, r)) : (s.subTo(i, s),
                            e && o.subTo(n, o),
                                a.subTo(r, a))
                        }
                        return 0 != s.compareTo(b.ONE) ? b.ZERO : a.compareTo(t) >= 0 ? a.subtract(t) : a.signum() < 0 ? (a.addTo(t, a),
                            a.signum() < 0 ? a.add(t) : a) : a
                    }

                    function Qt(t) {
                        var e, i = this.abs();
                        if (1 == i.t && i[0] <= $e[$e.length - 1]) {
                            for (e = 0; e < $e.length; ++e)
                                if (i[0] == $e[e])
                                    return !0;
                            return !1
                        }
                        if (i.isEven())
                            return !1;
                        for (e = 1; e < $e.length;) {
                            for (var s = $e[e], n = e + 1; n < $e.length && Pe > s;)
                                s *= $e[n++];
                            for (s = i.modInt(s); n > e;)
                                if (s % $e[e++] == 0)
                                    return !1
                        }
                        return i.millerRabin(t)
                    }

                    function Xt(t) {
                        var e = this.subtract(b.ONE)
                            , i = e.getLowestSetBit();

                            return !1;
                        var s = e.shiftRight(i);
                        t = t + 1 >> 1,
                        t > $e.length && (t = $e.length);
                        for (var n = y(), r = 0; t > r; ++r) {
                            var o = n.modPow(s, this);
                            if (0 != o.compareTo(b.ONE) && 0 != o.compareTo(e)) {
                                for (var a = 1; a++ < i && 0 != o.compareTo(e);)
                                    if (o = o.modPowInt(2, this),
                                    0 == o.compareTo(b.ONE))
                                        return !1;
                                if (0 != o.compareTo(e))
                                    return !1
                            }
                        }
                        return !0
                    }

                    function te() {

                    function ee(t) {

                    }

                    function ce(t, e) {

                        for (var i = new Array, s = t.length - 1; s >= 0 && e > 0;) {

                                i[--e] = n >> 6 | 192) : (i[--e] = 63 & n | 128,
                                i[--e] = n >> 6 & 63 | 128,

                    function he(t, e) {

                    }

                    function me(t, e) {
                        var i = new oe
                            , s = t >> 1;
                        this.e = parseInt(e, 16);
                        for (var n = new b(e, 16); ;) {
                            for (; this.p = new b(t - s, 1, i),
                                   0 != this.p.subtract(b.ONE).gcd(n).compareTo(b.ONE) || !this.p.isProbablePrime(10);)
                                ;

                                   0 != this.q.subtract(b.ONE).gcd(n).compareTo(b.ONE) || !this.q.isProbablePrime(10);)
                                ;

                                var r = this.p;
                                this.p = this.q,
                                    this.q = r
                            }
                            var o = this.p.subtract(b.ONE)
                                , a = this.q.subtract(b.ONE)
                                , c = o.multiply(a);
                            if (0 == c.gcd(n).compareTo(b.ONE)) {
                                this.n = this.p.multiply(this.q),
                                    this.d = n.modInverse(c),
                                    this.dmp1 = this.d.mod(o),
                                    this.dmq1 = this.d.mod(a),
                                    this.coeff = this.q.modInverse(this.p);
                                break
                            }
                        }
                    }

                    function ve(t) {
                        if (null == this.p || null == this.q)
                            return t.modPow(this.d, this.n);

                            e = e.add(this.p);
                        return e.subtract(i).multiply(this.coeff).mod(this.p).multiply(this.q).add(i)
                    }

                    function be(t) {

                    }

                    function ye(t) {

                        for (e = 0; e < t.length && t.charAt(e) != Le; ++e)

import time
import execjs
import requests
headers = {
    'Host': 'match.yuanrenxue.com',
    'Referer': 'http://match.yuanrenxue.com/match/6',
    'User-Agent': 'yuanrenxue.project',
    'X-Requested-With': 'XMLHttpRequest'
}

# express 服务调用
def get_m(timestamp, count):
    """ express 服务调用 """
    return requests.post('http://localhost:3000/encrypt', data={
        'timestamp': str(timestamp),
        'count': count
    }).text

q = ''
count = 0

all_data = []
for page in range(1, 6):
    count += 1
    timestamp = int(time.time()) * 1000
    m = get_m(timestamp,str(count))
    q += f'{str(count)}-{timestamp}|'
    params = {
        'page': page,
        'm': m,
        'q': q
    }
    print(params)
    url = 'http://match.yuanrenxue.com/api/match/6'
    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, params=params)
    print(response.json())
    all_data += response.json()['data']
total = 0
for each in all_data:
    num3 = int(each['value'])
    total += num3*(1+8+15)

print(total)
